        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can have performance drawbacks, especially when used in large datasets or within queries that process many rows. The function be executed once per row in a query, leading to potential performance bottlenecks. Optimizing the underlying query and ensuring efficient indexing on the dataset can mitigate some performance issues."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Potential Issues or Risks"
